ul.li:
Heads can only designate officers and employees of their government institution in the delegation
	orderconsultants or employees of other government institutions or from the
	private sector cannot be named in the delegation order;

Consideration of the Act's intent, which is
	to provide individuals with the right of access to their personal information, and of its limited and 
	specific exemptions;

Application of the Privacy Act, including:
The purpose of the Act;
The applicable definitions;
Their responsibilities, including the principles for assisting requesters;
Delegation, exemption decisions and the exercise of discretion;
The requirement to provide complete, accurate and timely responses; and
The complaint process and reviews by the courts;
